          <p class="supertitle">Full Time / Anywhere</p>
  <h1>Puppet Labs - Professional Services Engineer</h1>

  <div class="columns generic ">
    <div class="column main">
      <p><em>About Us:</em></p>

<p>We’re the company behind the leading open source data center automation project Puppet, which is written entirely in Ruby. We have a small team of top notch rubyists and sysadmins who are committed to keeping the leading open source automation product in a rapidly growing market ahead of the pack. Puppet Labs is an open source company that really believes in openness. Nearly every line of code you write for us will be published, and all of that will be discussed in our community as part of its acceptance process. This is your opportunity to help change how people do operations and to do so in a visible and reusable way.</p>

<p><em>Responsibilities:</em></p>

<ul>
<li>Help our Puppet Labs' customers succeed through training, consulting, and custom development engagements</li>
<li>Further Puppet Labs product growth with direct customer feedback</li>
<li>Expect to be traveling and engaged with clients much of the time.</li>
</ul>


<p><em>Requirements:</em></p>

<ul>
<li>Systems Adminstration experience/devops background</li>
<li>Puppet experience or other server management technology</li>
<li>Ability to speak in front of an audience and work with customers</li>
<li>Travel easily</li>
</ul>


<p><em>Gold Stars:</em></p>

<ul>
<li>A passion for Puppet itself and the Puppet community</li>
<li>CS, hard math/science background</li>
<li>Ruby</li>
<li>Sardonic wit</li>
<li>Large scale infrastructure experience</li>
</ul>

</div><!-- /.column.main -->

